	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Some corrections:<BR>
<BR>
1) Mobs [b]DO NOT[/b] have infinite mana.  Verant has said this on many occasions, and it is provable.  They regen it very quickly but you can drain them to 0.  If you want to see this, get some warriors, buff them with magic resistance and have them annoy a burynai cenobite, but don't kill it...  root it and have the warriors taunt and engage it hand to hand.  It will wrath and wrath, maybe 6 or 8 times, but then it will stop and be reduced to some small heals or straight melee.  If you leave it long enough, it will start wrathing again.  If you keep a caster mob going long enough they do run out of mana.  Presumably, therefore, you can mana seive them out of mana as well.  Whether or not this is a worthwhile thing to do depends on your tactics.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

