	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				NPC's definitely do not have infinite mana.  In my experience, enchanters can be quite good at draining mana, but not with this spell.  The easiest way to drain mana is...Charm!  Just charm something and have it fight something else.  Against a player an npc barely uses a portion of its mana pool to kill that player (two or three spells from a wizard can and have killed me).  Against another npc though they quickly burn through their entire mana pool, and sometimes, if they run out of mana from fighting multiple mobs you actually have to help them because npc casters melee pathetically against equivalently powered tanks (i.e. npc tanks).
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
